urlText: L2 Randwick and L3 Kingsford Line partial nightly service changes
content:
From Monday 19 October to Wednesday 21 October, nightly from 8pm to 1am, L2 Randwick and L3 Kinsford Line light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street on the L2 Randwick Line and the L3 Kingsford Line, due to planned utilities maintenance works in the CBD.

Each night the last L2 Randwick Line services:
  • Depart Randwick at 20:05, and end at Circular Quay at 20:42 
  • Depart Circular Quay at 20:48, and end at Randwick at 21:24 
Each night the last L3 Kingsford Line services:
  • Depart Juniors Kingsford at 20:00, and end at Circular Quay at 20:37 
  • Depart Circular Quay at 20:43, and end at Juniors Kingsford at 21:19 
If you are travelling between Circular Quay and Central Chalmers Street, use alternative transport, including nearby trains.

Normal full services between Circular Quay and Randwick or Juniors Kingsford will resume daily from 5am to 8pm.

Please allow extra travel time.
subtitle: L2 Randwick and L3 Kingsford Line partial nightly service changes

urlText: Trackwork between Sutherland and Hurstville
content:

  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Waterfall or Cronulla and Sutherland, and between Hurstville and Bondi Junction.
  • South Coast Line trains continue to run, some to a changed timetable.
  • On Thursday, buses replace the 00:45 Bondi Junction to Cronulla from Sydenham to Sutherland and the 00:55 Bondi Junction to Hurstville from Sydenham to Hurstville.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: T1 Western Line: Trackwork between Lidcombe and Strathfield
content:
Sunday 1 November
  • Buses replace trains between Lidcombe and Strathfield.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between:
    • Penrith and Lidcombe, then continue to Olympic Park
    • Penrith and Lindfield via the T3 Bankstown Line 
    • Richmond and Leppington via the T5 Cumberland Line
    • Lidcombe and the City via the T3 Bankstown Line (limited stops and all-stations)
    • Strathfield and the City
  • If you are travelling to the City or T1 North Shore Line stations, catch the direct train via Bankstown, or change at Lidcombe for a T3 Bankstown Line service.
  • Express buses also run between Blacktown and Strathfield or Central.
  • If you are travelling to Flemington, Homebush or Strathfield please change at Lidcombe for a bus. Change at Olympic Park for express buses to Strathfield.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
1T7: Olympic Park, then Strathfield and return
11T1: Blacktown, then express to Strathfield and return
55T1: Blacktown, then Central and return
67T1: Lidcombe, then all stations to Strathfield and return
subtitle: T1 Western Line: Trackwork between Lidcombe and Strathfield

properties.speechText:

  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.

urlText: Trackwork between Blacktown and Strathfield or Central.
content:
Sunday 1 November
  • Buses replace trains between Blacktown and Strathfield or Central. 
  • Trains from Blacktown towards Blue Mountains Line stations leave 35 minutes later than normal. 
  • Some trains between Bathurst and Lithgow also run to a changed timetable. 
  • Trains from Lithgow and Mount Victoria towards Blacktown run to the normal timetable. 
  • If you are travelling to Lithgow to connect with NSW TrainLink Regional Coaches please call 132 232 to confirm departure times. 
  • T1 Western Line trains run between Penrith and Olympic Park or the City via the T3 Bankstown Line. 
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
1T7: Olympic Park, then Strathfield and return
11T1: Blacktown then Strathfield and return
55T1: Blacktown, then Central and return
67T1: Lidcombe, then Flemington, Homebush, Strathfield and return
subtitle: Trackwork between Blacktown and Strathfield or Central.
